notes.note:
Rec'd this email from Progressive - 
Darryl Plug
Oct 8, 2020, 4:57 PM (16 hours ago)
to me

Looking to get approval to replace Tony’s engine for the following reason.

Vehicle presented with Check Engine Light on the dash. Scanned for codes and pulled code P0014 for Cam Performance. Technician proceeded to check the VVT Solenoid, as it has been recently replaced, and found the solenoid to be working as intended. The technician then proceeded to check the Timing Chain and found it to be stretched. The technician checked the oil level and found that the vehicle was down more than 2 liters of oil since the last oil change performed only 2782km’s ago. The vehicle is excessively burning oil with a documented burn rate of almost 1 liter of oil per 1000km’s. The constant loss of oil pressure from the excessive oil burn has caused the Timing Chain to stretch. Looking to get approval to replace Tony’s engine for the following reason.

The technician then proceeded to check the Timing Chain and found it to be stretched. notes.note:
High pressure fuel pump failed, contaminated whole system with metal filings.
Requires high pressure pump, injectors, fuel rails, in tank pump, drop fuel tank and clean, etc.
I called Unique Chrysler. Lynn confirmed this can happen. They have done one or two themselves. 
The high pressure pump is after the fuel filter. That is why the whole system gets contaminated.
Paying maximum liability of $4900. Total price = $9266.80 + HST. A.H.
